ined from the flux ratio.\nBecause the magnetic field is weaker than the typical value in the Galactic\nplane (3-10 \\mu G), the simple one-zone model may not work for HESS J1702-420\nand a significant fraction of the VHE gamma-rays may originate from protons.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 2 Jun 2011 07:35:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-28"}
